  "text": "In summary, further studies are required to investigate miR-10a function in vivo. Despite an intriguing expression pattern, we were not able to define the miR-10a function in Treg in vivo. Importantly, our results suggest that phenotypic effects obtained using antagomiRs and possibly other classes of pharmacological miRNA inhibitors should be interpreted with a certain degree of caution. Of note, similar discrepancies between pharmacological miRNA inhibition and genetic ablation have been described for another miRNA and other pharmacologic inhibitors [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
